Django SAML Integration with Keycloak
This project demonstrates how to integrate SAML-based Single Sign-On (SSO) in a Django application using Keycloak as the Identity Provider (IdP). This setup allows users to log in through Keycloak, establishing an SSO session, and access multiple endpoints within your application.

Features

- SAML authentication with Keycloak as the IdP
- Two Django Service Providers (SP1 & SP2) for cross-SP testing
- Docker-based Keycloak setup for easy development
- Single Logout (SLO) support with multiple logout types
- Modern responsive UI with beautiful animations
- Pre-configured realm with test user
- Comprehensive error handling and debugging
- Session-based authentication tracking

Requirements

- Python 3.x
- Django 5.1.2
- python3-saml library for SAML support
- Docker and Docker Compose (for Keycloak IdP)

Quick Start with Docker

1. Start Keycloak IdP: ./start-keycloak.sh
2. Start SP1: source venv/bin/activate && python3 manage.py runserver 127.0.0.1:8001
3. Start SP2: source venv/bin/activate && cd SAML_DJNAGO_2 && python3 manage.py runserver 127.0.0.1:8002
4. Check status: ./status.sh
5. Visit http://127.0.0.1:8001 or http://127.0.0.1:8002
6. Login with testuser/password123

Documentation

- DOCKER_SETUP.md: Complete Docker setup guide
- CONFIGURATION.md: Django configuration details
- KEYCLOAK_SETUP.md: Manual Keycloak setup instructions

refer https://medium.com/@vivekzs440/setup-sso-using-saml-in-django-using-keycloak-as-idp-b2b5d81c3534 for end to end setup
